Comparison is done first following Burnham & Anderson 2004:
if ___<2, then there is substantial support for the __i-th model (or the evidence against it is worth only a bare mention), and the proposition that it is a proper description is highly probable;
if 2<___<4, then there is strong support for the __i-th model;
if 4<___<7, then there is considerably less support for the __i-th model;
models with ___>10 have essentially no support.
